        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tui): handle German AltGr input",
        "body": "## Summary\n- ignore Kitty printable key-release events in the TUI custom editor so release events cannot duplicate text\n- decode German-layout AltGr Kitty CSI-u printable input when terminals report Ctrl+Alt plus a base-layout key\n- add regression coverage for AltGr @/€, ordinary Alt-modified input, and printable release events\n\n## Verification\n- pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/tui/components/custom-editor.ts src/tui/components/custom-editor.test.ts src/tui/tui.ts src/tui/tui.test.ts CHANGELOG.md\n- node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tui/components/custom-editor.test.ts src/tui/tui.test.ts\n- pnpm check:changed\n- git diff --check\n\n## Not Run\n- Live German keyboard / Kitty-terminal smoke test; this environment does not have that keyboard layout attached.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: TUI input should accept German-layout AltGr Kitty CSI-u printable characters such as `@` and `€`, while ignoring printable key-release events so releases do not duplicate text. This covers issue #48897 in `src/tui/components/custom-editor.ts`.\n- Real environment tested: Local Linux 6.19.14+kali-amd64 isolated worktree at PR head `6dfa6f45a0`; Node v22.22.2; pnpm 11.1.0. The smoke used a pseudo-terminal, raw stdin bytes, and the real `CustomEditor.handleInput(...)` path with `@earendil-works/pi-tui` key decoding.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  1. `git switch --detach origin/main` in the isolated proof worktree, then ran a Python PTY script that spawned `node --import tsx --input-type=module`, constructed `CustomEditor`, set stdin raw, and wrote Kitty CSI-u bytes to the PTY.\n  2. Repeated the same PTY/raw-stdin script at PR head `origin/pr-83947`.\n  3. `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.tui.config.ts src/tui/components/custom-editor.test.ts`\n- Evidence after fix: Terminal output from the PTY smoke:\n  ```\n  current main input bytes: ^[[64::113;7u ^[[8364::101;7u ^[[214;1u ^[[214;1:3u\n  current main RESULT {\"text\":\"ÖÖ\",\"length\":2}\n  PR head input bytes:    ^[[64::113;7u ^[[8364::101;7u ^[[214;1u ^[[214;1:3u\n  PR head RESULT {\"text\":\"@€Ö\",\"length\":3}\n\n  node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.tui.config.ts src/tui/components/custom-editor.test.ts\n  ✓ tui src/tui/components/custom-editor.test.ts (5 tests) 89ms\n  Test Files 1 passed (1)\n  Tests 5 passed (5)\n  ```\n- Observed result after fix: The same raw Kitty CSI-u stream that produced `ÖÖ` on current main produced `@€Ö` on the PR branch: AltGr `@` and `€` were inserted, the ordinary `Ö` press was inserted once, and the `Ö` release event was ignored instead of duplicating the character.\n- What was not tested: Did not test a physical German keyboard or the live Kitty terminal application; this environment does not have that keyboard layout attached. The smoke exercised the exact CSI-u bytes through a PTY/raw-stdin path instead.\n\nFixes openclaw/openclaw#48897\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-48897",
